Question One

Question Two

How many mission fields are blank? How many mission fields contain only spaces (one or more)?

grep(pattern = "^\\s*$", x = dat$mission, value = TRUE) %>% head(10) %>% pander()

listToNet <- function(x) {
    
    word.pairs <- list()
    
    for (i in 1:length(x)) {
        x.i <- x[[i]]
        word.pairs[[i]] <- NULL
        if (length(x.i) > 1) {
            word.pairs[[i]] <- data.frame(t(combn(x.i, 2)), stringsAsFactors = F)
            names(word.pairs[[i]]) <- c("from", "to")
        }
        
    }
    
    return(word.pairs)
    
}

Filter Graph by Tie Frequency

We can ignore word co-occurences that occue only once or twice across all missions (that would mean those two words occur together only once or twice in the sample - the co-occurence is not meaningful).

df.art$ties <- ties

df.art.filtered <-
   df.art %>%
   group_by( ties ) %>%
   mutate( n=n(), same.word= to == from ) %>%  # count frequency of each tie
   filter( n > 100, ! same.word ) %>% 
   ungroup() %>% 
   select( from, to ) %>% 
   unique()

listToNet <- function(x) {
    
    word.pairs <- list()
    
    for (i in 1:length(x)) {
        x.i <- x[[i]]
        word.pairs[[i]] <- NULL
        if (length(x.i) > 1) {
            word.pairs[[i]] <- data.frame(t(combn(x.i, 2)), stringsAsFactors = F)
            names(word.pairs[[i]]) <- c("from", "to")
        }
        
    }
    
    return(word.pairs)
    
}

Filter Graph by Tie Frequency

We can ignore word co-occurences that occur only once or twice across all missions (that would mean those two words occur together only once or twice in the sample - the co-occurence is not meaningful).

df.env$ties <- ties2

df.env.filtered <-
   df.env %>%
   group_by( ties ) %>%
   mutate( n=n(), same.word= to == from ) %>%  # count frequency of each tie
   filter( n > 25, ! same.word ) %>% 
   ungroup() %>% 
   select( from, to ) %>% 
   unique()

listToNet <- function(x) {
    
    word.pairs <- list()
    
    for (i in 1:length(x)) {
        x.i <- x[[i]]
        word.pairs[[i]] <- NULL
        if (length(x.i) > 1) {
            word.pairs[[i]] <- data.frame(t(combn(x.i, 2)), stringsAsFactors = F)
            names(word.pairs[[i]]) <- c("from", "to")
        }
        
    }
    
    return(word.pairs)
    
}

Filter Graph by Tie Frequency

We can ignore word co-occurences that occur only once or twice across all missions (that would mean those two words occur together only once or twice in the sample - the co-occurence is not meaningful).

df.edu$ties <- ties3

df.edu.filtered <-
   df.edu %>%
   group_by( ties ) %>%
   mutate( n=n(), same.word= to == from ) %>%  # count frequency of each tie
   filter( n > 160, ! same.word ) %>% 
   ungroup() %>% 
   select( from, to ) %>% 
   unique()
